people_also_ask.question: Has New Mexico ever been hit by a tornado?
people_also_ask.answer_source: Severe Weather Climatology for New Mexico
people_also_ask.answer_html: Most New Mexico tornadoes are relatively weak, and occurred in the afternoon and evening hours in the spring months. However, tornadoes can occur at any time. The graphs below illustrate New Mexico's tornado history.

people_also_ask.question: Has New Mexico been hit by a hurricane?
people_also_ask.answer_source: List of New Mexico hurricanes - Wikipedia
people_also_ask.answer_html: The inland U.S. state of New Mexico has experienced impacts from 81 known tropical cyclones and their remnants. There have been 68 known tropical cyclones from the Eastern Pacific that affected the state, compared to only 13 such Atlantic hurricanes.

value.text: The inland U.S. state of New Mexico has experienced impacts from 81 known tropical cyclones and their remnants. There have been 68 known tropical cyclones from the Eastern Pacific that affected the state, compared to only 13 such Atlantic hurricanes.

people_also_ask.question: What kind of storms does New Mexico have?
people_also_ask.answer_html: All 33 counties in New Mexico experience severe thunderstorms producing high winds, large hail, deadly lightning, and heavy rains at some time during the year. During the spring, from April through June, storms are at a peak mainly in the eastern areas of the state.
